SIMPLE: headless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Headless
<hw>Head"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>he⟦aacute⟧fodle⟦aacute⟧s</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having no
head; beheaded; <as>as, a <ex>headless</ex> body, neck, or
carcass</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Destitute of a chief or leader.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Raleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Destitute of understanding or prudence; foolish;
rash; obstinate; mindless.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Witless headiness in judging or <qex>headless</qex> hardiness in
condemning.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Headlight</ent>⟦br⟧
